# Fasting-Atlas Project Instructions

## 1. Project Overview
* [cite_start]**Goal**: A multilingual AI platform to convert heterogeneous scientific publications into a structured, method-aware database of human experimental data[cite: 4, 6].
* [cite_start]**Core Value**: Transforming ~150 years of literature into a traceable database for quantitative analysis across populations and historical periods[cite: 6, 17].
* [cite_start]**Domain Agnostic**: While named "Fasting-Atlas," the system should work for any human experimental data domain[cite: 7].

## 2. Core Information Layers
Every paper processed must be decomposed into these distinct layers:
* [cite_start]**Metadata**: Authors, year, journal, study design, and demographics[cite: 20].
* [cite_start]**Methods & Participants (Priority)**: Detailed descriptions of assays, instruments, dosing, and timing[cite: 22, 23]. 
    * [cite_start]*CRITICAL*: Must account for methodological shifts (e.g., 1925 copper-reduction vs. modern enzymatic assays)[cite: 25].
* [cite_start]**Narrative Results**: Qualitative statements and reported trends in text[cite: 26].
* [cite_start]**Tables**: Structured numerical data extraction[cite: 27].
* [cite_start]**Figures/Graphs**: Extracting raw numerical values and individual datapoints from plots[cite: 28, 31].

## 3. Implementation Rules & Constraints
* **Multilingualism**: Support English, German, and Russian. [cite_start]Include OCR, machine translation, and preservation of original text[cite: 51, 52, 53, 56].
* **Traceability Requirement**: Every datapoint MUST link to:
    * [cite_start]Original paper and specific location within the document[cite: 59, 60].
    * [cite_start]Measurement method and units used[cite: 61, 62].
    * [cite_start]Extraction method (Auto vs. Manual) and confidence level[cite: 64, 65].
* [cite_start]**Quality Control (CouncilLLM)**: Use independent AI extraction processes and flag discrepancies for human validation[cite: 68, 69].
* [cite_start]**Data Integrity**: Accuracy is prioritized over processing speed[cite: 68].

## 4. Technical Context for AI Assistant
* [cite_start]**Input Types**: Modern PDFs, scanned historical papers, embedded tables, and graphical plots[cite: 10, 11, 12, 13, 14].
* **Semantic Analysis Goals**:
    * [cite_start]Map historical terminology to modern equivalents[cite: 44].
    * [cite_start]Identify variables even if terminology differs[cite: 40].
    * [cite_start]Detect relationships (e.g., "higher in group A than B")[cite: 41].
* [cite_start]**Search Strategy**: Enable natural-language search and conceptual similarity grouping across the corpus[cite: 45, 46].